Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.13,0:00:03.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, all you viewers out there!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.83,0:00:07.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When you're watchin' Fairy Tail, make \Nsure to keep the room nice and bright,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.13,0:00:09.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and sit back from the screen, 'kay?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.15,0:00:13.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Happy, where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.65,0:00:14.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.12,0:00:20.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They left me behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.48,0:00:23.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to head to where Natsu \Nis while I have the chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.22,0:00:51.63,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be all right! I'll yell it out countless times.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.63,0:00:56.70,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe your every tomorrow will be shining.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.70,0:00:59.05,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,The intersection of all people
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.05,0:01:01.66,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,whose dreams have come true is one point:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.66,0:01:06.29,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,Never giving up.  And that's why we're not gonna lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.29,0:01:11.47,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,When it seems like you'll be blown away by the headwinds,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.47,0:01:13.62,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,grasp this hand, try to take a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.62,0:01:16.89,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you're not alone anymore, got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.01,0:01:22.00,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,Go forward, more and more!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.00,0:01:24.52,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give up on your awesome dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.52,0:01:25.78,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, don't cry!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.78,0:01:27.25,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,Move on, my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.25,0:01:29.63,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, with the light shining down upon you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.63,0:01:31.71,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't even think about something like giving up!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.71,0:01:34.14,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you trade being hurt again for strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.14,0:01:39.63,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,Your eyes, always looking straight ahead,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.63,0:01:43.91,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,can surely see the light!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.20,0:02:05.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not gonna be won over by this \Nkiddy kitty merchandise, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.39,0:02:13.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.88,0:02:18.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Voice of Darkness!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.89,0:02:26.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We rose up for our freedom, and to save Jellal.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.00,0:02:32.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't underestimate "Mad Dog" Wally!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.46,0:02:35.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're tough thanks to all \Nthat "training" you gave us!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.34,0:02:37.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.18,0:02:51.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This guy isn't sayin' a peep! What a bore...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.06,0:02:56.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You keep puttin' up a brave face, and \Nyou'll end up like that girl from before. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.00,0:02:57.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, brat! 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.18,0:03:02.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you realize how sacred a cause \Nit is to erect this R-system? 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.03,0:03:06.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,At the moment this tower is completed, \Nall of you will get to go to heaven!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.74,0:03:10.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The R-system will resurrect our god!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.76,0:03:11.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up, pig...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.87,0:03:13.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.31,0:03:14.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let him be.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.83,0:03:17.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna have to help suppress \Nthe rebellion this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.91,0:03:23.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll continue the ceremony as many times as \Nit takes until you learn to revere our god!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.35,0:03:27.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,God?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.91,0:03:29.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need anything like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.25,0:03:34.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need a god that \Ncan't even save one child.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.36,0:03:39.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hatred...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.25,0:03:42.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hate...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.41,0:03:45.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.77,0:03:47.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate them, and their god...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.68,0:03:49.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything about this world...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.79,0:03:55.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hate! And I will devour that hatred...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.23,0:03:59.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,People's hatred makes me grow stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.48,0:04:01.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.64,0:04:04.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What amusing fools.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.25,0:04:07.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm right here among them...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.67,0:04:10.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet they trouble themselves to resurrect me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.04,0:04:12.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,To give me a body?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.56,0:04:14.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.73,0:04:17.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how fiercely they believe,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.31,0:04:22.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,one cannot sense my presence \Nwithout strong hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.43,0:04:25.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jellal...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.05,0:04:27.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You are quite the lucky one!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.39,0:04:30.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You got to meet the god that they worship so!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.90,0:04:36.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Zeref!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.53,0:04:40.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My existence is hatred itself...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.05,0:04:46.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to liberate Sector 8 today!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.75,0:04:47.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, keep it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.78,0:04:50.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible! The guard is too tight there!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.48,0:04:53.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But we have to hurry and save Jellal or...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.39,0:04:57.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You ain't got a prayer, Mr. Simo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.74,0:05:02.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Erza! A-Are you in love with Jellal?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.06,0:05:05.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you bringing that up now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.14,0:05:07.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now is not the time to...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.05,0:05:09.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've always...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.91,0:05:14.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Simon!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.48,0:05:16.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.41,0:05:18.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic Troops!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.33,0:05:20.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Simon!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.52,0:05:22.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.13,0:05:37.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.11,0:05:38.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, don't give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.78,0:05:40.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got to fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.43,0:05:41.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Outta the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.63,0:05:45.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.75,0:05:49.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Save... Jellal...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.05,0:05:54.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.05,0:05:56.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Erza!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.15,0:06:06.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa Rob!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.13,0:06:10.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My magical power may have withered, \Nbut I can still protect my friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.55,0:06:15.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I will not allow such young life to perish!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.78,0:06:27.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.99,0:06:29.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He reflected the magic back!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.13,0:06:33.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.48,0:06:39.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps I have been of some use, despite \Nme being such a decrepit old man...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.44,0:06:44.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,For a wizard, one's magical power is \Nthe same as their life energy itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.98,0:06:50.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And when this old man lost his magic, \NI was brought to this sorry state...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.27,0:06:56.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Erza, your possibilities are still endless!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.91,0:06:58.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.13,0:07:01.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.33,0:07:03.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Heart?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.52,0:07:08.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. Everything begins from \Nbelieving from your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.07,0:07:15.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,For example, you can think of horoscopes,\Nfaith, and prayer as forms of magic. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.14,0:07:20.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They are miracles that only \Npeople who believe can sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.13,0:07:22.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Only those who believe?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.46,0:07:24.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.06,0:07:28.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Only those who believe in the power of \Nmagic, believe their your own power,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.62,0:07:34.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and believe in living in harmony \Nwith nature are able to use magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.42,0:07:37.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.18,0:07:39.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.81,0:07:45.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When I grow up, I want to become a witch \Nand ride on a broom and fly in the sky!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.80,0:07:47.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you'll be able to.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.37,0:07:50.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll fly free, in the wide open sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.40,0:07:55.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'll let you ride too, Grandpa!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.69,0:08:03.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think I'd see a smile \Nlike that in a place like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.75,0:08:05.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.31,0:08:08.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Freedom is inside of your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.21,0:08:11.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no freedom in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.55,0:08:16.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I am sure that your dream \Nwill come true, Erza...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.72,0:08:20.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I will grant your wish!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.73,0:08:22.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.27,0:08:26.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.41,0:08:30.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Freedom is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.90,0:08:35.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Erza, retreat! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.03,0:08:36.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.08,0:08:37.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Er-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.20,0:09:02.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.06,0:09:02.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.85,0:09:04.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even the Magic Troops...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.85,0:09:06.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis can use magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.40,0:09:09.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is... magic...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.39,0:09:12.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.69,0:09:16.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,With this power, I can save Jellal!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.42,0:09:21.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Flying in the sky will have \Nto wait for now, Grandpa.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.21,0:09:23.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.15,0:09:26.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...will gain my freedom!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.60,0:09:29.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Follow me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.13,0:09:33.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what are we going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.80,0:09:34.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.50,0:09:39.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.49,0:09:42.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We were just acting under orders!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.74,0:09:43.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Out of my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.25,0:09:49.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jellal!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.94,0:09:53.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.60,0:09:55.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all over!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.09,0:09:57.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We fought, just like you said to, Jellal!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.99,0:10:03.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Simon's seriously injured, and \NGrandpa Rob shielded me...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.22,0:10:06.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There are a great number of other \Npeople who sacrificed their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.49,0:10:08.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But we won!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.20,0:10:09.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We've gained our freedom!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.30,0:10:11.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.32,0:10:13.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wally and the others have taken their boats.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.67,0:10:15.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We can get off this island!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.08,0:10:18.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Erza...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.80,0:10:21.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no more running away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.60,0:10:25.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,True freedom is right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.18,0:10:28.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ooh, it's a movie lacrima!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.99,0:10:30.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.28,0:10:32.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a lacrima that stores the data of a movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.64,0:10:34.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's a moovee?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.35,0:10:35.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A story!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.86,0:10:39.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Actors act out a drama for us to watch!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.16,0:10:40.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's the first time I \Never saw one myself though...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.33,0:10:47.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Too bad for you, Tony Joe.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.90,0:10:50.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,From the moment you met me...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.25,0:10:53.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...your fate was sealed, get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.84,0:10:55.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How austere!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.14,0:10:56.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's kinda hard-edged...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.84,0:10:58.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's how a dandy should be!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.81,0:11:00.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't get it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.26,0:11:03.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis is late...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.14,0:11:06.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jella, what are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.96,0:11:09.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's escape from this island together!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.17,0:11:12.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Erza, there is no freedom in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.99,0:11:16.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I realized that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.45,0:11:20.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It is not transient freedom that we require.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.53,0:11:23.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's {\i1}true{\i0} freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.80,0:11:27.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Zeref's world!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.40,0:11:38.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can understand their feelings a bit now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.21,0:11:41.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They were trying to resurrect \Nthis Zeref person, see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.05,0:11:46.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But these pitiful believers couldn't \Neven sense Zeref's presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.64,0:11:48.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.74,0:11:51.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This tower is mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.95,0:11:53.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I will complete it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.56,0:11:55.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I will resurrect Zeref.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.79,0:12:00.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.78,0:12:03.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Save me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.06,0:12:06.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it, Jellal!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.27,0:12:08.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.65,0:12:12.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you hate them, Erza?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.38,0:12:13.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate them, but this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.84,0:12:14.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's no good!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.75,0:12:18.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't be able to sense Zeref like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.88,0:12:19.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.17,0:12:25.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jellal!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.33,0:12:26.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.60,0:12:27.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.21,0:12:35.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Erza, let's complete the R-system... \NI mean, the Tower of Heaven, together!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.32,0:12:38.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we can resurrect Zeref.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.10,0:12:39.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop saying such crazy things!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.79,0:12:42.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to get off this island!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.45,0:12:55.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine. If you want to go so badly, then \Nyou can leave this island on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.29,0:12:56.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,On my own?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.76,0:12:59.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The rest of them are all mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.37,0:13:02.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Completing this tower will \Ntake a lot of work, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.76,0:13:05.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.14,0:13:07.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not like them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.03,0:13:11.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give everyone clothes, and food, and rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.70,0:13:18.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fear and oppression does give rise to hatred, \Nbut the work efficiency is far too poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.96,0:13:20.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.61,0:13:24.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone is already on the \Nships, waiting for us!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.82,0:13:28.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No one is planning on coming \Nback here and working!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.28,0:13:32.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's because they never explained \Nto us the meaning behind the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.57,0:13:34.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I will show them the meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.70,0:13:38.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They will work for the glory \Nof the great Wizard Zeref!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.17,0:13:40.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But... who would choose to \Ncontinue sacrificing themselves?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.79,0:13:42.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sacrifice?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.60,0:13:45.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what I need now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.39,0:13:47.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Zaref taught me, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.59,0:13:51.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jellal, please, open your eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.47,0:13:53.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My eyes are already open.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.36,0:13:56.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no more need for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.30,0:13:58.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,However I will allow you to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.19,0:14:01.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Since you eliminated all those \Nwho stood in my way for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.37,0:14:06.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You will leave this island and have \Nyour fill of that transient freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.05,0:14:07.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jellal...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.15,0:14:10.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But you will never speak of this to anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.67,0:14:14.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If the government finds out about this Tower \Nof Heaven, it will be quite troublesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.91,0:14:20.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you try to tell someone, I will have \Nto destroy this tower and everyone in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.58,0:14:23.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You are also forbidden to come near here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.11,0:14:24.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you set even one foot...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.25,0:14:26.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I think that'll do...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.90,0:14:29.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,First, I will make Sho disappear...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.83,0:14:31.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jellal...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.47,0:14:35.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That will be your freedom!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.24,0:14:39.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Live knowing that your friends' \Nlives hang on your shoulders, Erza!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.64,0:15:18.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I... will fight Jellal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.07,0:15:30.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We have no other option than firing \NEtherion from the Satellite Square!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.05,0:15:34.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The R-system is a forbidden magic that \Nmust be erased from the annals of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.92,0:15:37.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You do understand what this \Nmeans, right everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.78,0:15:41.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,An attack from Etherion will \Nreturn everything to nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.22,0:15:43.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if there are citizens there!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.51,0:15:48.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And Jellal, your younger twin brother, \Nwill disappear as well, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.21,0:15:50.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.40,0:15:52.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've come to terms with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.51,0:15:56.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All of us came this far due \Nto the sacrifices of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.69,0:15:59.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That is the Magic World of today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.16,0:16:00.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Elder Leiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.44,0:16:03.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It will go down in history that our\Ncountry committed the crime
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.15,0:16:07.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,of attacking the land of\NKa Elm without provocation!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.00,0:16:10.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That means we'll have to \Nsacrifice ourselves as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.85,0:16:12.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Elder Belno!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.03,0:16:14.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The dead cannot return to life!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.65,0:16:19.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When it comes time to teach the children how \Nprecious life is, that is what we must say!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.61,0:16:21.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We must put an end to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.67,0:16:24.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I concur with firing Etherion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.55,0:16:26.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Only one more...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.85,0:16:29.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Only one more, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.90,0:16:32.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,One more and then it is game over.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.60,0:16:39.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fish...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.71,0:16:43.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We played our hearts out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.51,0:16:45.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way... Where are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.27,0:16:49.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a second, Erza.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.37,0:16:52.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That Zeref that was in your story...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.00,0:16:54.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, you should know about Zeref too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.78,0:17:00.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pretty sure they called that monster that \Ncame out of the Lullaby one of Zeref's demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.36,0:17:02.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.15,0:17:06.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I suspect that Deliora was \Nalso one of the Zeref's demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.14,0:17:12.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And Jellal is trying to \Nresurrect this Zeref person?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.25,0:17:14.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand his motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.59,0:17:17.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sho... One of my friends in the past...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.64,0:17:22.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He said something about when the resurrection \Nwas complete, they'd become rulers over heaven...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.10,0:17:27.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But what I don't understand is why \Nyour past allies turned against you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.35,0:17:31.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't the traitor Jellal and not you, Erza?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.80,0:17:36.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He must have indoctrinated them \Nsomehow after I disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.75,0:17:40.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But I left them here for 8 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.97,0:17:42.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The fact is, I did betray them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.29,0:17:46.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But it was for their sake!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.20,0:17:46.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.80,0:17:48.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough, Lucy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.57,0:17:53.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If I can defeat Jellal, this will all be over.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.72,0:17:56.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that really the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.80,0:18:04.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Whether I win or lose this battle, \NI will vanish from this world...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.28,0:18:07.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Those words are really bothering me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.91,0:18:11.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sister... That story...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.61,0:18:14.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that supposed to mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.27,0:18:15.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sho...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.91,0:18:19.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You trying to get sympathy from \Nyour pals with that tall tale?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.20,0:18:20.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a break!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.46,0:18:21.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not even close to the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.11,0:18:27.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You blew up our ships and ran away by yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.61,0:18:32.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If Jellal hadn't noticed your betrayal, \Nwe would have all sunk into the sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.71,0:18:38.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jellal told us that was the fate of those who \Ndidn't learn the proper way to use magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.78,0:18:44.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You were drunk from the power of magic! You \Ntried to rid yourself of all of us and your past!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.28,0:18:49.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jellal told you this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.14,0:18:52.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that something the Erza \Nyou know would have done?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.92,0:18:58.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.65,0:19:02.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know anything about us!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.05,0:19:06.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Only Jellal's words were able to save us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.35,0:19:11.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we spent these past \N8 years finishing this tower!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.65,0:19:12.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,For Jellal...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.79,0:19:16.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If... it was all a lie...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.38,0:19:23.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you are right, Sis... And Jellal is wrong...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.32,0:19:24.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.56,0:19:28.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.46,0:19:30.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Please wait, Gray-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.57,0:19:35.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Back then, he purposefully \Nattacked your ice-clone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.31,0:19:36.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.55,0:19:40.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no way a user of darkness \Ntechniques would not be able to notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.78,0:19:45.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Juvia came here to ascertain \Nhis true intentions.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.65,0:19:49.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see Phantom's Element 4 \Ndeserves their reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.60,0:19:51.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.46,0:19:56.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sho, I put on a performance to both trick \Nyou and get them to come to the tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.63,0:20:01.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Why? Why would you...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.89,0:20:03.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sho...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.60,0:20:06.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone has been fooled by Jellal.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.30,0:20:09.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I played the fool as well \Nuntil the time was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.77,0:20:11.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Simon, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.68,0:20:14.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I believed in you, Erza.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.59,0:20:17.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I always did for these past 8 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.42,0:20:23.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad we could meet, Erza.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.52,0:20:24.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,From the bottom of my heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.81,0:20:25.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Simon...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.27,0:20:31.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.55,0:20:35.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How could you believe in her so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.07,0:20:37.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.88,0:20:42.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why wasn't I able to believe in her?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.50,0:20:48.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.20,0:20:51.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What is the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.94,0:20:54.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What should I believe in?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.20,0:21:03.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be difficult to accept it all at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.55,0:21:07.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But let me say this much...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.51,0:21:13.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,For these past 8 years, I have \Nnever forgotten about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.80,0:21:17.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't do anything for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.90,0:21:22.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry I was so weak...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.96,0:21:25.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But now you can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.54,0:21:26.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.30,0:21:30.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been waiting for this \Nmoment for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.77,0:21:33.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Waiting for a number of powerful \Nwizards to gather here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.87,0:21:35.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Powerful wizards?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.61,0:21:38.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,To fight Jellal.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.98,0:21:41.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll all work together.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.00,0:21:50.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,First, we have to prevent Wally \Nand Salamander from clashing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.35,0:21:55.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with this room?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.67,0:21:57.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's kitty-city.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.16,0:22:00.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ooh, I like this one!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.21,0:22:02.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a helmet!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.61,0:22:05.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.10,0:22:06.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Aye, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.64,0:22:09.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Or something...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.50,0:22:12.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.10,0:22:16.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I... can't get it off...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.95,0:22:19.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,D'oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.00,0:22:22.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's funny so whatever!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.67,0:22:24.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dandy...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.29,0:23:58.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! I win again!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.98,0:24:00.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's 9 wins in a row.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.55,0:24:01.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Play me again!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.49,0:24:03.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This time I'm going to win, for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.91,0:24:06.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Natsu, you say that every time.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.60,0:24:08.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm tired already.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.71,0:24:10.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I win by default, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.86,0:24:13.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! I win!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.73,0:24:16.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: Heaven's Game
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.39,0:24:19.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's against the rules to \Nchange the rules unilaterally!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.51,0:24:21.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Freeedddooom!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.23,0:24:24.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, I think he broke.
